T1  - Impression Management in the Feedback-Seeking Process: A Literaturereview and Research Agenda
AU  - Morrison, Elizabeth Wolfe
AU  - Bies, Robert J.
Y1  - 1991/07/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1991.4279472
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1991.4279472
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 522
EP  - 541
VL  - 16
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Although impression management in the Feedback-seeking process has emerged as an important research topic, existing research has failed to capture the range and complexity of impression management behaviors. This article provides a theoretical framework for existing and future research. It examines how impression management sometimes discourages and at other times encourages feedback inquiry, and it explains the impact that impression management has on when, from whom, and how individuals ask for feedback. Organizational implications of the impression management motive in feedback seeking are discussed.
AB  - Although impression management in the Feedback-seeking process has emerged as an important research topic, existing research has failed to capture the range and complexity of impression management behaviors. This article provides a theoretical framework for existing and future research. It examines how impression management sometimes discourages and at other times encourages feedback inquiry, and it explains the impact that impression management has on when, from whom, and how individuals ask for feedback. Organizational implications of the impression management motive in feedback seeking are discussed.
